    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-09-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-09-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="33" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d33">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Thompson</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Petropolis</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-09-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 6, 1893</hi>
                        </date>.
                            (Received September 7.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Thompson reports that the navy of Brazil has revolted, assumed complete
                        control over the harbors, and seized all the war vessels. It has made no
                        attack but threatens, unless the vice-president resigns, to bombard Rio de
                        Janeiro.</p>
            </div>
